author: cmpilato
msg: Improve the output from svnsync (hopefully in time to not have 1.4.0
stuck with the previous state).
* subversion/svnsync/main.c
(commit_callback): Print "Committed revision X." instead of
"Committing rev X".  We've got 80 columns to work with here, so
there's no need to abbreviate.  And the commit is completed
already, so fix the verb tense.
(copy_revprops): Print progress to stdout, similar to message
printed by commit_callback().
* subversion/tests/cmdline/svnsync_tests.py
(run_sync): Updated comment noting expected stdout.

author: dlr
msg: On the merge-tracking branch: Attempt to clarify the doc string for an

* subversion/libsvn_client/client.h
(svn_client__path_relative_to_root): Be more explicit about the need
for a non-null REPOS_ROOT or RA_SESSION param.
